<p>Kansas City residents can take advantage of several solar incentives to reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% credit on total system costs through 2032, stepping down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. While Missouri doesn't offer state-level solar rebates, the state does exempt solar installations from sales tax and provides property tax exemptions for the added home value from solar systems. Evergy offers interconnection programs for solar customers, though they don't currently provide cash rebates. Additionally, Kansas City residents may qualify for federal tax credits, and some financing options include power purchase agreements (PPAs) and solar loans that require little to no money down, making solar accessible to a broader range of homeowners.</p>

