<p>When selecting a solar installer in Kansas City, prioritize companies with proper Missouri contractor licensing, NABCEP (North American Board of Certified Energy Practitioners) certified installers, and strong local references. Look for installers who offer comprehensive warranties covering panels (typically 20-25 years), inverters (10-25 years), and workmanship (minimum 10 years). Reputable Kansas City solar companies should provide detailed production estimates based on your specific roof conditions and local weather patterns, handle all permitting and interconnection paperwork with Jackson County and Evergy, and offer financing options. Request multiple quotes, verify insurance coverage, check Better Business Bureau ratings, and ensure the company has experience with Missouri's interconnection requirements and local building codes.</p>

